</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Pullover Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>&nbsp;Position yourself on a bench, lying on your back with your head and upper back supported. Plant your feet firmly on the floor.</li>



<li>Grasp a dumbbell with both hands, holding it above your chest with your arms extended. Maintain a slight bend at the elbows.</li>



<li>As you exhale, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head in an arc, keeping your arms slightly bent. Stop when you feel a deep stretch in your lats and chest.</li>



<li>Inhale as you engage your lats and chest to pull the dumbbell back to the starting position above your chest.</li>



<li>Repeat as necessary.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">TipsÂ </h4>



<ul>
<li>Lower the dumbbell until you feel a good stretch in your lats and chest. But avoid overstretching to prevent potential shoulder strains.</li>



<li>Maintain a slight bend in your arms throughout the movement. This not only helps to protect the elbow joints but also enhances tension in the targeted muscles.</li>



<li>Focus on squeezing your core during the movement to stabilize and prevent excessive arching of your lower back. Excessive arching can lessen muscle activation of the lats.</li>
</ul>



